14/06/2010
CAPE TOWN, South Africa -- Slovenia scored its first victory in a world football championship Sunday (June 13th), defeating Algeria by 1-0.
The goal came from the captain of the Slovenians, Robert Koren, in the 79th minute.
The other Group C match between England and the United States ended in a draw, 1-1, giving Slovenia a lead in the group.
Slovenia plays the US on Friday.
(AFP, AP, FIFA website - 13/06/10)
